Here's the `c-avatar` component with RDFa annotations and size variants via `data-state`.

## HTML

```html
<div
  class="c-avatar"
  typeof="mcs:Component"
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Displays a user profile image with fallback initials"
  data-state="medium"
>
  <img
    class="c-avatar__image"
    src="https://i.pravatar.cc/150?u=john-doe"
    alt="John Doe"
    property="mcs:hasPart" resource="#avatar-image"
  />
  <span
    class="c-avatar__initials"
    property="mcs:hasPart" resource="#avatar-initials"
    aria-hidden="true"
  >
    JD
  </span>
</div>
```

## CSS

```css
/* =============================================
   c-avatar — Atom
   Displays user profile image with fallback initials
   ============================================= */

/* Base — medium (default) */
.c-avatar {
  position: relative;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: var(--space-12);
  height: var(--space-12);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  background-color: var(--color-brand-200);
  overflow: hidden;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.c-avatar__image {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
}

.c-avatar__initials {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  pointer-events: none;
  user-select: none;
}

/* Hide initials when image is present */
.c-avatar__image:not([src=""]) ~ .c-avatar__initials,
.c-avatar__image[src]:not([src=""]) ~ .c-avatar__initials {
  display: none;
}

/* =============================================
   Size variants via data-state
   ============================================= */

/* Small */
.c-avatar[data-state="small"] {
  width: var(--space-8);
  height: var(--space-8);
}

.c-avatar[data-state="small"] .c-avatar__initials {
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
}

/* Medium (default — already defined above) */
.c-avatar[data-state="medium"] {
  width: var(--space-12);
  height: var(--space-12);
}

.c-avatar[data-state="medium"] .c-avatar__initials {
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
}

/* Large */
.c-avatar[data-state="large"] {
  width: var(--space-16);
  height: var(--space-16);
}

.c-avatar[data-state="large"] .c-avatar__initials {
  font-size: var(--font-size-title);
}
```

## Design Decisions

1. **No margin on root** — The `c-avatar` component declares no margin, following the Golden Rule. External spacing is handled by layout classes.

2. **Fallback initials** — The `c-avatar__initials` element is hidden via `display: none` when a valid `src` is present on the image. This uses the adjacent sibling combinator (`~`) for a clean, CSS-only fallback.

3. **Size via `data-state`** — Three sizes (small, medium, large) are controlled by `data-state` attributes, not class modifiers. This aligns with the state management rule.

4. **RDFa annotations** — The root element declares `typeof="mcs:Component"`, `mcs:taxonomyLevel="mcs:Atom"`, and a purpose description. The image and initials are marked as `mcs:hasPart` for compositional clarity.

5. **Token-driven** — All values use `var(--token)` references. No magic numbers appear anywhere in the CSS.

6. **Accessibility** — The initials element has `aria-hidden="true"` since it's a visual fallback, not content. The image has meaningful `alt` text.

# c-badge Component — Status Indicator

## HTML

```html
<div 
  class="c-badge" 
  typeof="mcs:Component" 
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Displays status indicators with semantic color states"
  data-state="default"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="none"
  data-mcs-consequence="Visual status indication only"
>
  <span class="c-badge__dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Status Label</span>
</div>
```

## CSS

```css
/* Layer: Component */
.c-badge {
  /* Root — NO margin per Golden Rule */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-1);
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  background-color: var(--color-background-primary);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border-default);
  transition: background-color var(--transition-fast), border-color var(--transition-fast), color var(--transition-fast);
}

/* Dot indicator */
.c-badge__dot {
  display: inline-block;
  width: var(--space-1);
  height: var(--space-1);
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-full);
  background-color: currentColor;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

/* Semantic color states via data-state */
.c-badge[data-state="success"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-success);
  border-color: var(--color-border-success);
  color: var(--color-text-success);
}

.c-badge[data-state="warning"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-warning);
  border-color: var(--color-border-default);
  color: var(--color-text-warning);
}

.c-badge[data-state="error"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-error);
  border-color: var(--color-border-error);
  color: var(--color-text-error);
}

.c-badge[data-state="info"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand);
  border-color: var(--color-border-interactive);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
}

/* Default state (neutral) */
.c-badge[data-state="default"] {
  background-color: var(--color-gray-100);
  border-color: var(--color-border-default);
  color: var(--color-text-secondary);
}
```

## Usage Examples

```html
<!-- Success badge -->
<div class="c-badge" data-state="success">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Active</span>
</div>

<!-- Warning badge -->
<div class="c-badge" data-state="warning">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Pending</span>
</div>

<!-- Error badge -->
<div class="c-badge" data-state="error">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Failed</span>
</div>

<!-- Info badge -->
<div class="c-badge" data-state="info">
  <span class="c-badge__dot"></span>
  <span class="c-badge__label">Updated</span>
</div>
```

## Design Decisions

1. **Atom taxonomy**: Badge is a self-contained, indivisible UI primitive — no composition with other components needed.

2. **State via data-state**: Semantic colors (success, warning, error, info) are controlled through `data-state` attributes, not class modifiers, following MCSS state management rules.

3. **No margin on root**: The `.c-badge` root selector declares zero margin — spacing is delegated to layout components (`l-stack`, `l-cluster`) as required by the Golden Rule.

4. **Dot indicator**: The `c-badge__dot` element provides a visual cue that reinforces the semantic state. It uses `currentColor` to automatically match the text color of each state.

5. **Token-driven**: All values reference MCSS design tokens — no magic numbers, no hardcoded colors. The badge uses `--border-radius-full` for pill shape, `--space-1`/`--space-2` for compact padding, and semantic color tokens for each state.

6. **Accessibility**: The dot has `aria-hidden="true"` since it's decorative. The label text provides the meaningful content. The component has no interaction type since it's purely visual.

Here's the **c-button** component — an MCSS Atom with four variants and three states, fully annotated with RDFa and token-driven CSS.

---

## HTML

```html
<button
  class="c-button"
  typeof="mcs:Component"
  property="mcs:taxonomyLevel" content="mcs:Atom"
  property="mcs:purpose" content="Trigger an action or submission"
  data-variant="primary"
  data-state="default"
  data-mcs-interaction-type="click"
  data-mcs-consequence="Initiates the associated action"
  data-mcs-triggers-event="c-button:action"
>
  <span class="c-button__label">Submit</span>
  <span class="c-button__spinner" hidden aria-hidden="true">
    <svg class="c-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" height="16">
      <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3" fill="none" stroke-dasharray="31.4 31.4" stroke-linecap="round">
        <animateTransform attributeName="transform" type="rotate" from="0 12 12" to="360 12 12" dur="0.8s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
      </circle>
    </svg>
  </span>
</button>
```

---

## CSS

```css
/* =============================================
   c-button — Atom
   Layer: component (c-*)
   ============================================= */

.c-button {
  /* Layout & sizing */
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  gap: var(--space-2);
  padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-5);
  border: 2px solid transparent;
  border-radius: var(--border-radius-md);
  cursor: pointer;
  user-select: none;

  /* Typography */
  font-family: var(--font-family-sans);
  font-size: var(--font-size-body);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  line-height: var(--line-height-base);

  /* Visual */
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  transition:
    background-color var(--transition-fast),
    border-color var(--transition-fast),
    color var(--transition-fast),
    box-shadow var(--transition-fast);

  /* Accessibility */
  outline-offset: 2px;

  /* NO margin — Golden Rule */
}

/* ---- Focus ---- */
.c-button:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--color-border-focus);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* ---- Hover ---- */
.c-button:hover:not([data-state="disabled"]) {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand-hover);
}

/* ---- Active / Press ---- */
.c-button:active:not([data-state="disabled"]) {
  transform: scale(0.97);
}

/* =============================================
   Variants (data-variant)
   ============================================= */

/* Primary (default) */
.c-button[data-variant="primary"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand);
  color: var(--color-text-on-brand);
  border-color: transparent;
}
.c-button[data-variant="primary"]:hover:not([data-state="disabled"]) {
  background-color: var(--color-background-brand-hover);
}

/* Secondary */
.c-button[data-variant="secondary"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-secondary);
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border-color: var(--color-border-default);
}
.c-button[data-variant="secondary"]:hover:not([data-state="disabled"]) {
  background-color: var(--color-gray-100);
  border-color: var(--color-border-interactive);
}

/* Outline */
.c-button[data-variant="outline"] {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-brand-600);
  border-color: var(--color-brand-600);
}
.c-button[data-variant="outline"]:hover:not([data-state="disabled"]) {
  background-color: var(--color-brand-50);
  color: var(--color-brand-700);
  border-color: var(--color-brand-700);
}

/* Ghost */
.c-button[data-variant="ghost"] {
  background-color: transparent;
  color: var(--color-text-primary);
  border-color: transparent;
}
.c-button[data-variant="ghost"]:hover:not([data-state="disabled"]) {
  background-color: var(--color-gray-100);
  color: var(--color-brand-600);
}

/* =============================================
   States (data-state)
   ============================================= */

/* Loading */
.c-button[data-state="loading"] {
  cursor: wait;
  pointer-events: none;
  opacity: 0.8;
}
.c-button[data-state="loading"] .c-button__spinner {
  display: inline-flex;
}
.c-button[data-state="loading"] .c-button__label {
  opacity: 0.7;
}

/* Disabled */
.c-button[data-state="disabled"] {
  cursor: not-allowed;
  pointer-events: none;
  opacity: 0.45;
  background-color: var(--color-gray-200);
  color: var(--color-gray-500);
  border-color: var(--color-gray-200);
}

/* Error */
.c-button[data-state="error"] {
  background-color: var(--color-background-error);
  color: var(--color-text-error);
  border-color: var(--color-border-error);
  animation: c-button-shake 0.3s ease-in-out;
}
.c-button[data-state="error"]:hover:not([data-state="disabled"]) {
  background-color: var(--color-red-100);
  border-color: var(--color-red-500);
}

/* ---- Shake animation for error state ---- */
@keyframes c-button-shake {
  0%, 100% { transform: translateX(0); }
  20%      { transform: translateX(-4px); }
  40%      { transform: translateX(4px); }
  60%      { transform: translateX(-3px); }
  80%      { transform: translateX(3px); }
}

/* =============================================
   Elements
   ============================================= */

.c-button__label {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: var(--space-1);
}

.c-button__spinner {
  display: none;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
}

/* =============================================
   Sizes (optional — data-size)
   ============================================= */

.c-button[data-size="sm"] {
  padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-3);
  font-size: var(--font-size-caption);
}
.c-button[data-size="lg"] {
  padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
  font-size: var(--font-size-title);
}
```

---

## Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| **`data-variant` instead of class modifiers** | Aligns with MCSS state/data convention; avoids `--modifier` pollution on an Atom |
| **`data-state` for loading/disabled/error** | Follows the Golden Rule: state is data, not a class modifier |
| **No margin on root** | Golden Rule — spacing is delegated to layout (`l-stack`, `l-cluster`) |
| **Spinner as child element** | Keeps the button self-contained; shown/hidden via `data-state="loading"` |
| **Shake animation on error** | Provides immediate, accessible feedback without relying on color alone |
| **`data-size` as optional attribute** | Keeps the component flexible without bloating the core variant set |
| **All values use `var(--token)`** | Zero magic numbers — fully token-driven |
| **`data-mcs-interaction-type` + `data-mcs-consequence`** | Enables behavioral documentation and event-driven architecture |

---

## Usage Examples

```html
<!-- Primary (default) -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="primary" data-state="default">Save</button>

<!-- Secondary -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="secondary" data-state="default">Cancel</button>

<!-- Outline -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="outline" data-state="default">Learn More</button>

<!-- Ghost -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="ghost" data-state="default">Dismiss</button>

<!-- Loading -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="primary" data-state="loading">Saving…</button>

<!-- Disabled -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="primary" data-state="disabled" disabled>Submit</button>

<!-- Error -->
<button class="c-button" data-variant="primary" data-state="error">Failed — Retry</button>
```

---

This component is ready for integration into any MCSS-based design system. It respects all five layers, avoids margin violations, and provides clear, accessible interaction feedback.

